  "text": "Phonological awareness tests: these tests were designed for the purpose of the current study based on [CITATION_1] . 1) Phonemes Count: The child heard 15 items in ascending order according to their level of difficulty. For each item, the child was asked to count the phonemes. While counting each phoneme, he/she was asked also to clap his/her hands or knock on the desk. Three examples were given prior to the actual test (α = .767).",
